    - "CPython source: Modules/itertoolsmodule.c"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: itertools iterator __name__.__len__() for count, cycle, repeat, chain, islice, product, pairwise, batched."
    - "itertools.count.__name__ == 'count' — count is a C extension type; __name__ is 'count' (5 chars). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.cycle.__name__ == 'cycle' — cycle is a C extension type; __name__ is 'cycle' (5 chars). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.repeat.__name__ == 'repeat' — repeat is a C extension type; __name__ is 'repeat' (6 chars). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.chain.__name__ == 'chain' — chain is a C extension type; __name__ is 'chain' (5 chars). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.islice.__name__ == 'islice' — islice is a C extension type; __name__ is 'islice' (6 chars). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.product.__name__ == 'product' — product is a C extension type; __name__ is 'product' (7 chars). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.pairwise.__name__ == 'pairwise' — pairwise is a C extension type added in 3.10; __name__ is 'pairwise' (8 chars). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.batched.__name__ == 'batched' — batched is a C extension type added in 3.12; __name__ is 'batched' (7 chars). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

